President Trump, speaking off the record, discussed the possibility of releasing a Middle East peace plan next week. He expressed his desire to broker a deal between Benny Gantz and Benjamin Netanyahu, but acknowledged that it would be difficult. The President mentioned that the election has delayed the release of the plan, but both candidates are interested in pursuing peace. He stated that the plan is "a great plan" that would work, and hinted at inviting Palestinian leaders to discuss it at the White House. Trump emphasized the importance of achieving peace in the region and expressed optimism about the upcoming meetings with both candidates.